* Lehao - Undo command bug fixes

The previous undo has such a bug: when delete person and then undo, the client list of the affected appointment will not be refreshed (undo). This is because a state simply copy the reference of the schedule, and different schedules in different states actually refer to the same appointment and same client list. To solve this we need to create deep copy when initialize the state and get schedule of the state.

Update JsonSerializableSchedule to check for conflicts
commitResults.messageBody:
The user might make changes to the json file to include appointments with time conflicts.

Implementing a check in JsonSerializableSchedule allows us to ensure that even if the user changes appointments such that there are time conflicts, the schedule will not contain conflicting appointments

User might make a mistake and duplicate appointments in the JSON file, which causes the appointment list to be wiped.

Refraining from adding duplicate appointment to the schedule allows us to ensure that we can rectify user mistakes while not wiping their current data.

User might modify their JSON file and create duplicated Persons, which causes their data to be wiped.

Refraining from adding a duplicate person allows us to rectify the user's mistake without wiping their data.

User might make a mistake in modifying their person JSON file, which would cause all the Person data to be wiped.

Wiping the schedule data, when person data is wiped would ensure that there will be no appointments with Persons that are not stored in the app.

commitResults.messageBody:
It is possible to start with a sample schedule, and the user's own contacts.
This would show discrepancies between the schedule and the user's contacts.

Using a boolean to track whether sampleSchedule was used, allows us to ensure
that if there is a case where schedule.json was missing, but contacts.json was
found, we would not have discrepancies between the two lists.
